6. Benefits Gained from Factory Pattern
•	Open/Closed Principle achieved — adding a new database type (e.g. Oracle) requires only a new class and one dictionary entry, never touching existing code
•	Parameter pollution eliminated — Redis now genuinely cannot accept a charset parameter, proven by a real failing test when attempted
•	Each connection type is independently testable — bugs in MySQL logic cannot affect MongoDB tests
•	Constructor complexity reduced — RedisConnection takes 3 parameters instead of inheriting all 11 from the original monolithic class
•	New developers reading MySQLConnection see only MySQL-relevant code — no need to mentally filter out irrelevant branches
•	The if/elif chain is permanently eliminated — replaced with a dictionary lookup that scales without growing in complexity

